verses.text: And it shall be, when thou \add art\add* come in unto the land which the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God giveth thee \add for\add* an inheritance , and possessest it, and dwellest therein;

That thou shalt take of the first of all the fruit of the earth , which thou shalt bring of thy land that the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God giveth thee, and shalt put \add it\add* in a basket , and shalt go unto the place which the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God shall choose to place his name there.

And thou shalt go unto the priest that shall be in those days , and say unto him, I profess this day unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God , that I am come unto the country which the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* sware unto our fathers for to give us.
And the priest shall take the basket out of thine hand , and set it down before the altar of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God.

And thou shalt speak and say before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God , A Syrian ready to perish \add was\add* my father , and he went down into Egypt , and sojourned there with a few , and became there a nation , great , mighty , and populous :
And the Egyptians evil entreated us, and afflicted us, and laid upon us hard bondage :

And when we cried unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* God of our fathers , the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* heard our voice , and looked on our affliction , and our labour , and our oppression :
And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* brought us forth out of Egypt with a mighty hand , and with an outstretched arm , and with great terribleness , and with signs , and with wonders :
And he hath brought us into this place , and hath given us this land , \add even\add* a land that floweth with milk and honey.

And now, behold, I have brought the firstfruits of the land , which thou, O 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, hast given me. And thou shalt set it before the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God , and worship before the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God :

And thou shalt rejoice in every good \add thing\add* which the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God hath given unto thee, and unto thine house , thou, and the Levite , and the stranger that \add is\add* among you. \p

¶ When thou hast made an end of tithing all the tithes of thine increase the third year , \add which is\add* the year of tithing , and hast given \add it\add* unto the Levite , the stranger , the fatherless , and the widow , that they may eat within thy gates , and be filled ;

Then thou shalt say before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God , I have brought away the hallowed things out of \add mine\add* house , and also have given them unto the Levite , and unto the stranger , to the fatherless , and to the widow , according to all thy commandments which thou hast commanded me: I have not transgressed thy commandments , neither have I forgotten \add them:\add*

I have not eaten thereof in my mourning , neither have I taken away \add ought\add* thereof for \add any\add* unclean \add use\add*, nor given \add ought\add* thereof for the dead : \add but\add* I have hearkened to the voice of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* my God , \add and\add* have done according to all that thou hast commanded me.
Look down from thy holy habitation , from heaven , and bless thy people Israel , and the land which thou hast given us, as thou swarest unto our fathers , a land that floweth with milk and honey. \p
¶ This day the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God hath commanded thee to do these statutes and judgments : thou shalt therefore keep and do them with all thine heart , and with all thy soul.

Thou hast avouched the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* this day to be thy God , and to walk in his ways , and to keep his statutes , and his commandments , and his judgments , and to hearken unto his voice :
And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath avouched thee this day to be his peculiar people , as he hath promised thee, and that \add thou\add* shouldest keep all his commandments ;

And to make thee high above all nations which he hath made , in praise , and in name , and in honour ; and that thou mayest be an holy people unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* thy God , as he hath spoken.
